==Scots==
===Etymology===
Old English [[maþa]], from Germanic ''*maþa-'' ‘worm’, from Indo-European ''*math-, *moth-'' used for insects and vermin.  Cognate with Dutch [[made]], German [[Made]] and related to Swedish [[mask]], Danish [[madike]], archaic English [[maddock]] (English [[maggot]])

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /meɪð/

===Noun===
'''mathe'''
# a [[grub]], a [[maggot]], an [[earthworm]]

